GstOpenMAX

GStreamer OpenMAX IL wrapper

You'll need an OpenMAX IL implementation. Luckily STMicroelectronics has
provided an useful sample implementation in the Bellagio project which is Open
Source.

== How to build omxil ==

Download the source code from:

http://omxil.sourceforge.net/
http://dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/omxil/libomxil-B-0.3.2.tar.gz

Install as usual:

 ./configure --prefix="$HOME/omx"
 make
 make install

Register the components:

 $HOME/omx/bin/omxregister

== How to build gst-openmax ==

If you are fetching it from CVS:

 ./autogen.sh --noconfigure

Assuming you have libomxil installed in "$HOME/omx":

 ./configure --prefix="$HOME/omx" --with-pkg-config-path=$HOME/omx/lib/pkgconfig

 make

Then as root (depending on your prefix).

 make install

Finally you can try it:

 export GST_PLUGIN_PATH=$HOME/omx/lib/gstreamer-0.10
 gst-launch-0.10 filesrc location="test.mp3" ! omx_mp3dec ! alsasink
 gst-launch-0.10 filesrc location="test.ogg" ! omx_vorbisdec ! alsasink

NOTE: The omx_mp3dec element only works if you compiled omxil with mad support.

== Links ==

* http://omxil.sourceforge.net/
* http://freedesktop.org/wiki/GstOpenMAX
